    intro: 'Transmission failure is one of the most financially devastating mechanical events a vehicle owner can experience. An automatic transmission rebuild or replacement on a common Japanese vehicle typically costs between $4,000 and $8,000. For European models or complex dual-clutch transmissions (DCTs), costs can reach $12,000–$18,000. For most used vehicle owners, a transmission failure without insurance cover effectively renders the vehicle a write-off — the repair cost exceeds what the vehicle is worth. MBI policies with drivetrain cover specifically address this risk.',
